  • Low Correlation Assets: These assets move independently from the rest of the portfolio, providing unique sources of return and risk. Including these assets can potentially improve the portfolioâs risk-adjusted returns and stability.

  • High Correlation Assets: These securities tend to move in sync with other holdings in the portfolio. They offer less diversification benefit as their performance is closely tied to existing positions. While they may still be valuable for other reasons (e.g., high expected returns), they contribute less to reducing overall portfolio risk through diversification.
